Prediction of Whether sequence is generated or not based on Library concentration.


Call:
glm(formula = generated ~ library_conc_nm, family = binomial, 
    data = nextseq)

Coefficients:
                Estimate Std. Error z value Pr(>|z|)    
(Intercept)      0.96779    0.09679   9.998   <2e-16 ***
library_conc_nm  0.28903    0.01817  15.906   <2e-16 ***

Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1

    Null deviance: 2499.8  on 5806  degrees of freedom
Residual deviance: 2056.3  on 5805  degrees of freedom
AIC: 2060.3

    (Intercept) library_conc_nm 
       2.632131        1.335132 
Area under the curve: 0.841
  1. The log-odds of the sequence is generated when library concentration is 0 is 0.96779, that means model predicts a 72.46% probability of sequence generation at baseline.
  2. Log-Odds at library Concentration = 1 is (0.96779 + 0.28903). That means odds = 4.88, and model predict a 77.84% probability of sequence being generated at library Concentration = 1.
  3. Every one unit increase in the library concentration lead the probability of increase in the sequence generation by 5.39%.
  4. P value = 2e-16, suggesting library concentration is a significant predictor of whether sequence is generated or not.

Count of Sequence Generation by Library concentration and Cluster Density.

Boxplot of Library Concentration and Cluster Dendity by Sequence

Density of Sequence generation by Library concentration.

count of sequence between cluster density between 150 to 230 (K/mm2).

Code 
nextseq %>% 
  filter(cluster_density >= 150 & cluster_density<= 230) %>%
  group_by(sequence) %>%
  mutate(
    sequence = factor(sequence, 
                           levels = c("Yes", "No", "QNS"))
    ) %>% 
  summarise(count = n()) %>% 
  gt() %>% 
    tab_header(
    title = "count of sequence between cluster density between 150 to 230 (K/mm2)"
  )
count of sequence between cluster density between 150 to 230 (K/mm2)
sequence count
Yes 2218
No 84
QNS 40
